(the native form of this personal name is kovacsicz mónika. this article uses the western name order.) mónika kovacsicz (born 20 november 1983) is a hungarian handballer of yugoslav origin who plays for ferencvárosi tc and the hungarian national team. her first major international tournament was the 2005 world championship, where she finished third with the hungarian team. she was present on another world championship (2007) and took part on three european championships (2006, 2008, 2010). she also competed at the 2008 summer olympics in beijing, capturing a fourth place. kovacsicz won the champions league with viborg in 2009.